    "faq": [
      {
        "question": "Does this skill create GitHub issues directly?",
        "answer": "No. This skill provides templates and guidance for writing comprehensive issues. You then use gh CLI or GitHub web interface."
      },
      {
        "question": "What makes a ticket comprehensive?",
        "answer": "A comprehensive ticket includes background context, current vs desired state, specific requirements as checkboxes, edge cases, and file locations."
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I use this with private repositories?",
        "answer": "Yes. The templates work for any GitHub repository. Ensure you have appropriate permissions to create or edit issues."
      },
      {
        "question": "Is my data safe when using this skill?",
        "answer": "Yes. This is a prompt-based skill with no code execution. It only generates text templates. No data is sent to external services."
      },
      {
        "question": "How is this different from GitHub issue templates?",
        "answer": "GitHub issue templates are static forms. This skill provides dynamic guidance that adapts to your specific context."
      },
      {
        "question": "Should I create a new ticket or update an existing one?",
        "answer": "Create a new ticket for new work items. Update an existing ticket when expanding vague issues or adding new requirements."
      }
